    question: "Is it okay to let my 10-year-old stay home for just 15 minutes?",
    answer: "For many mature 10-year-olds, a 15-minute 'trial run' is an excellent way to build independence. Ensure they know how to lock the door, how to reach you, and what to do if the phone rings or someone knocks. If the child remains calm and follows all rules during these short intervals, you can gradually increase the time (Safe Kids, 2023).",
